 -- Matthias Klumpp <mak@debian.org>  Wed, 21 Feb 2018 20:38:26 +0100

apper (0.9.2+git20161222-3) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Enable AppStream icon download explicitly
  * Don't install the updater Plasmoid (Closes: #851117)
    - The updater Plasmoid is currently broken and will need some
      work to be revived. We can not ship with it for Debian Stretch.
      Having two default-enabled updater icons also is very confusing
      to users, so if the updater gets ported to recent QtQuick and
      received upstream fixes, we can bring it back as separate package.

 -- Matthias Klumpp <mak@debian.org>  Thu, 19 Jan 2017 20:45:22 +0100

